Subject: [PATCH 8/8] Multi-window support: auto-assign unique ports per terminal session

Each terminal gets its own independent proxy+CLI pair with no shared state,
eliminating the "zsh: killed" issue when opening claude in multiple windows.

Key changes:
- Per-port PID and log files (proxy-5529.pid, proxy-5530.pid, etc.)
- Auto-detect when base proxy is already running via port lsof check
- Auto-assign next available port for each new terminal session
- Mach-O binary validation before exec to diagnose corruption
- JXPROXY_MULTI env var: auto (default), yes (always new port), no (legacy)
